Matt De G , 06/15/2014

Perfect!

This app is perfect. Not only is it specifically designed for those with food allergies (nuts, dairy, wheat, gluten, etc.) you can customize it to let it tell you what to avoid based on your specific diet needs. So, if you want to avoid foods with high fructose corn syrup, or eat foods high in protein, or avoid foods low in saturated fat, anything specific, then this app does that too! The scanner is fast and accurate, letting you know to "avoid" it and why or letting you know if the food is good for you based on your diet/allergies. It will even rate the food for you on a percentage scale and gives you better suggestions to increase what it is you want to intake more of!


Just be careful as the scanner will not pick up the "no frills" food versions. For instance, any supermarket branded bar codes will not scan. If you buy the "Key Food" brand cereal or bread it will not find the product.

El Waylondo , 07/24/2012

Interesting

So, it makes grocery shopping take a little longer. So, it seems a little inconsistent in the ratings it gives to some foods, and some of the alternate choices are completely alien to me. Still, this app gives me the ability to scan nearly any item in the grocery store and quickly confirm or debunk the claims of the manufacturer.


It is so simple that it is almost too vague. Basically, point it at a food item's bar code and it will give you a number between 0 and 100, 100 being extremely healthy. If that is not clear enough, then you can go by color;


Green = good

Yellow = maybe

Red = bad


Its biggest saving grace is in taking away false claims from the product manufacturers. I was quite surprised by how many so-called 'healthy' foods were revealed to be poor diet choices. For this, and because this app is just so entertaining in the grocery store and in the pantry, I give it four stars.
